🚀 How to Run
Clone this repository or download the FRAP.R file to your local machine.

Open your R console or RStudio.

Run the application using the following command:

R
library(shiny)
runApp("path/to/directory/containing/FRAP.R")
📄 Input Data Format
The application expects tabular data (preferably .csv) with the following column structure. The app utilizes intelligent column detection, so exact naming is flexible, but the following keywords are recommended:

Time (e.g., Time, Frame, t)

ROI Intensity (e.g., ROI, Intensity, Bleach, Signal)

Background Intensity (e.g., Background, bg, bkg)

Reference Intensity (e.g., Reference, ref). Note: If no reference column is found, the app will default to a constant value of 100.

